            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EBoasting%20is%20verbalized%20pride.%20It%20is%20self-commendation%2C%20bragging%20to%20others%20of%20our%20accomplishments.%20However%2C%20all%20that%20actually%20matters%20is%20what%20God%20thinks%20of%20us%2C%20not%20what%20others%20think.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBoasting%20is%20the%20exact%20opposite%20of%20the%20meekness%20and%20gentleness%20of%20Christ.%20Paul%20refused%20to%20boast%20about%20his%20personal%20appearance%2C%20power%2C%20or%20accomplishments.%20Instead%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20his%20strength%20was%20a%20hidden%20force%2C%20unnoticed%20by%20the%20world%20but%20divinely%20powerful%20(2%20Corinthians%2010%3A3-4).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20used%20his%20God-given%20authority%2C%20not%20for%20destruction%2C%20but%20for%20building%20up%20(2%20Corinthians%2010%3A8).%20He%20gave%20reports%20about%20the%20mission%20work%20he%20had%20accomplished%2C%20not%20to%20brag%20about%20what%20he%20had%20done%2C%20but%20to%20show%20what%20had%20been%20done%20by%20the%20grace%20of%20God.%20Without%20a%20doubt%2C%20Paul%20knew%20that%20%22the%20person%20who%20wishes%20to%20boast%20should%20boast%20only%20of%20what%20the%20Lord%20has%20done%22%20(2%20Corinthians%2010%3A17).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIsaiah%20foresaw%20a%20day%20in%20which%20%22pride%20will%20be%20brought%20low%20and%20the%20Lord%20alone%20will%20be%20exalted%22%20(Isaiah%202%3A11).%20Satan's%20proud%2C%20boasting%20spirit%20will%20one%20day%20be%20brought%20low%2C%20and%20no%20one%20will%20dare%20utter%20a%20boast%20against%20the%20Lord.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22Let%20him%20who%20boasts%20boast%20in%20the%20Lord%22%20(2%20Corinthians%2010%3A17%20NIV).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
